title: AlbuRIOT (Unity/Photon)

# Scope
- Do NOT edit: `Assets/Photon/`, `Assets/TextMesh Pro/`, `Assets/Imported Assets/`, `Library/`, `Temp/`, `Packages/`, `*.meta`, `obj/`, `bin/`.
- New code under `Assets/Scripts/` (Player, Enemies, Managers, UI, Combat, NPC, Map, Inventory, etc.).
- After code changes: output a short "Unity setup" checklist if inspector/prefab work is needed.

# Project Overview
AlbuRIOT is a multiplayer survival game (up to 4 players) inspired by Philippine mythology.
Primary systems:
- procedural map generation (`Assets/Scripts/Map/TerrainGenerator.cs`, `MapResourcesGenerator.cs`)
- enemy ai and combat (`Assets/Scripts/Enemies/BaseEnemyAI.cs`, per-creature AI under `Assets/Enemies/`)
- power-steal progression (`Assets/Scripts/Combat/PowerStealManager.cs`)
- ability system (`Assets/Scripts/Combat/Abilities/AbilityBase.cs`)
- moveset/combat style system (`Assets/Scripts/Managers/MovesetManager.cs`)
- inventory and equipment (`Assets/Scripts/Inventory/`, `Assets/Scripts/Equipments/`)
- quest/objective system (`Assets/Scripts/Managers/QuestManager.cs`, `Assets/Scripts/Items/QuestData.cs`)
- encyclopedia/bestiary system (`Assets/Scripts/Encyclopedia/`)
- shrine offering system (`Assets/Scripts/Managers/ShrineManager.cs`)
- tutorial system (`Assets/Scripts/Managers/TutorialManager.cs`)
- co-op multiplayer via Photon PUN 2

