# Key Singletons (DontDestroyOnLoad)
- `QuestManager.Instance` — quest state, objective tracking, multiplayer sync
- `GameManager.Instance` — game state, scene management
- `SceneLoader.Instance` — async scene loading with loading screens
- `ItemManager.Instance` — runtime item database
- `NetworkManager.Instance` — Photon connection/room management
- `LocalUIManager.Instance` — exclusive UI panel management
- `EncyclopediaManager.Instance` — enemy discovery/bestiary tracking, persistent via PlayerPrefs
- `AlbuRIOTIntegrationManager.Instance` — cross-system wiring, auto-connects core managers
- `MemoryCleanupManager.Instance` — centralized memory cleanup on scene change/room leave
- `MultiplayerScalingManager.Instance` — scales enemy stats/spawns by player count
- `NunoManager.Instance` — tutorial NPC guidance, skill HUD gating
- `LoadingScreenManager` — async scene loading with animated loading panel
- `GlobalPlaymodeCleanup` — clean Photon disconnect on quit, static `IsQuitting` flag
- `NunoDialogueBarUI.Instance` — bottom-screen dialogue bar for Nuno NPC

Scene-scoped (no DontDestroyOnLoad):
- `LocalInputLocker` — per-scene input lock stack
- `CutsceneManager` — per-scene cutscene playback
- `DialogueManager` — per-scene dialogue
- `FirstMapLoadingScreen` — first-map-specific loading screen (singleton, scene-scoped)

# Style (C#)
- `[SerializeField] private` for inspector; PascalCase for classes/methods, camelCase for fields.
- No static mutable shared state; use instance/scoped data for multiplayer.
- keep comments lowercase and concise

# Core Coding Rules
- read the full target script before modifying it
- apply fixes directly and iterate until stable
- keep all systems multiplayer-safe and scalable
- provide step-by-step Unity inspector/setup notes whenever assignments are required
- keep code/file organization clear and structured

# Photon (critical)
- All gameplay actions MUST use `[PunRPC]` and `photonView.RPC()`. Only `photonView.IsMine` owners mutate state; others read-only.
- Spawn/destroy: `PhotonNetwork.Instantiate()` / `PhotonNetwork.Destroy()` when in room.
- AI ticks only on `PhotonNetwork.IsMasterClient` (or offline).
- only move/control local-owned players (`PhotonView.IsMine`)
- keep master client authoritative for shared quest state and synchronized transitions
- avoid duplicate spawns by checking for existing local player first
- use RPC buffering carefully to avoid stale state across scene changes
- when iterating players, always use `PlayerRegistry.All` — never `FindWithTag("Player")`

# Centralized Spawn And Transition Flow
Use a single spawn pipeline for all maps.

Single source of truth:
- `Assets/Scripts/Managers/PlayerSpawnCoordinator.cs` (static utility class)

Callers that must use the coordinator:
- `Assets/Scripts/Managers/MapTransitionManager.cs`
- `Assets/Scripts/Managers/ProceduralMapLoader.cs`
- `Assets/Scripts/Managers/CutsceneManager.cs` (WaitForPlayerAndSetup)

Rules:
- do not create map-specific spawn handlers
- do not duplicate spawn selection/teleport logic in other scripts
- all scene-entry player placement must go through `EnsureLocalPlayerAtSpawn(...)`
- generated scene markers must use `SpawnMarker_#` naming
- map-generated marker flow should come from `MapResourcesGenerator`

Spawn fallback order:
1. `PlayerSpawnManager.nextSpawnPosition`
2. `SpawnMarker_*` objects in active scene
3. `MapResourcesGenerator.GetSharedSpawnPositions()`
4. `TutorialSpawnManager.spawnPoints`
5. `NetworkManager.spawnPoints`
6. terrain center fallback

# Player Spawning
- 4 player prefabs: `playerPrefab`, `playerPrefab2`, `playerPrefab3`, `playerPrefab4`
- prefab index = `PhotonNetwork.LocalPlayer.ActorNumber - 1`
- `TutorialSpawnManager` (class in `SpawnManager.cs`) handles instantiation
- `PlayerRegistry` tracks all active `PlayerStats`:
  - `PlayerRegistry.All` — iterate all players (use this, never `FindWithTag("Player")`)
  - `PlayerRegistry.GetLocalPlayerTransform()` — local player

# Quest System
- `QuestManager` (singleton, `MonoBehaviourPun`, `IPunObservable`, `IInRoomCallbacks`)
- quest data defined in `QuestData.cs` — `Quest` has `QuestObjective[]` array
- objective types: `Kill`, `Collect`, `TalkTo`, `ReachArea`, `FindArea`, `ShrineOffering`, `PowerSteal`, `Custom`
- master-authoritative for Kill/ReachArea/etc.
- `Collect` and `TalkTo` are per-player: each player must complete individually before quest advances
- quest UI shows "Complete - waiting for other players (X/4)" when locally done
- pickup quest progress: `ItemPickup.UpdateQuestProgress()` → `AddProgress_Collect`
- inventory backup: `QuestManager.OnInventoryItemAdded` → `ScheduleInventoryReconcile()` (1-frame delay)
- `QuestJsonLoader` / `ShopTradeJsonLoader` — load quest/trade definitions from JSON in `Resources/`

# Inventory And Equipment
- `Inventory` (`MonoBehaviourPun`, `IPunObservable`) — per-player component
- events: `OnItemAdded`, `OnInventoryChanged`, `OnItemRemoved`, `OnSlotChanged`
- `Inventory.FindLocalInventory()` uses `PlayerRegistry.GetLocalPlayerTransform()` first
- `QuestManager.EnsurePlayerInventory()` handles subscribe/unsubscribe via `lastInventoryRef` tracking
- `QuestManager.RefreshPlayerInventory()` forces re-resolution after spawn/scene transition
- **never manually subscribe to inventory events outside `EnsurePlayerInventory()`** — prevents double subscription
- `EquipmentManager` — per-player, resolves hand bone via `HumanBodyBones.RightHand`
- scene transition: `Inventory.CacheLocalInventory()` / `EquipmentManager.CacheLocalEquipment()` before load, auto-restore in `Awake()`

# Enemy AI
- Base: `BaseEnemyAI` in `Assets/Scripts/Enemies/`. BT nodes in `Assets/Scripts/Enemies/BehaviorTree/`.
- Use `isBusy`, `BeginAction()`/`EndAction()`, `globalBusyTimer`; run attack logic in coroutines; guard with `!PhotonNetwork.IsMasterClient` return in Update.
- per-creature scripts: `Assets/Enemies/<CreatureName>/<CreatureName>AI.cs`
- creatures: Amomongo, Aswang Queen, Aswang Unit, Bad Diwata-Punso, Bakunawa, Berberoka,
  Bungisngis, Busaw, DiwataPunso, Kapre, Manananggal, Minokawa, Pugot, Sarimanok,
  Shadow Touched Diwata, Sigbin, Sirena, Tikbalang, Tiyanak, Wakwak
- `EnemyData` (ScriptableObject) for stats/loot
- `MapEnemyDirector` / `PerlinEnemySpawner` for procedural placement
- `EnemyCampEncounter` — self-contained camp system: spawns enemies, tracks defeats, grants team buffs (master-authoritative)
- `NightHuntModifier` — runtime `EnemyData` override for night enemies (creates runtime SO copy)
- shared utilities in `Assets/Enemies/1COMMON/`: `BeamMover`, `DestroyAfterSeconds`, `EnemyDamageZone`, `EnemyProjectile`

# Damage And Status Effect Routing
- player damage: `DamageRelay.ApplyToPlayer()`
- enemy damage: `EnemyDamageRelay.Apply()` (static, network-safe)
- status effects: `StatusEffectRelay.Apply()` (static, types: Slow, Root, Silence, Stun, DefenseDown, Bleed, StaminaBurn)
- `PlayerDamageOnTrigger` — generic hazard/trap trigger component

# Ability And Moveset System
- `AbilityBase` (abstract ScriptableObject, namespace `AlbuRIOT.Abilities`) — cooldown, icon, `Execute()`
- `MovesetManager` (`MonoBehaviourPun`, per-player) — combat style switching, syncs via buffered RPC
- `MovesetData` / `SpecialMoveData` (ScriptableObjects) — attack stats, special moves, VFX, audio

# Input And UI Locking
- `LocalInputLocker.Ensure()` — named lock stack with per-owner tracking
- `LocalUIManager.Ensure()` — exclusive UI panel ownership
- after cutscene/transition, release stale locks and call `ForceGameplayCursor()`

# MapResourcesGenerator Notes
- avoid `PhotonNetwork.Destroy` for scene/local PhotonViews (ViewID <= 0); use local `Destroy`
- non-owner clients should not network-destroy generated objects; require `pv.IsMine` or MasterClient
- clear existing `SpawnMarker_*` before recreating from buffered RPCs
- deterministic names + pre-spawn cleanup for map guide objects

# Gameplay/Design Preferences
- camera: 3rd person (`ThirdPersonCameraOrbit`)
- movement: wasd (`ThirdPersonController`)
- inventory: per-player
- UI/UX and art/audio must align with `storyline.txt` and `alburiot.txt`
- chapter progression and level content must align with `Assets/docs/CHAPTER 1 - 3.md`

# Key Paths (quick reference)
- Player: `PlayerStats`, `ThirdPersonController`, `PlayerCombat`, `PlayerAnimatorSync`
- Combat: `AbilityBase`, `PlayerCombat`, `DebuffManager`, `DamageRelay`, `EnemyDamageRelay`
- Inventory: `Inventory`, `InventoryUI`, `ItemManager`; use `Inventory.FindLocalInventory()` for multiplayer
- Managers: `GameManager`, `NetworkManager`, `QuestManager`, `CutsceneManager`, `NunoShopManager`, `ShopTradeJsonLoader`
- UI: TextMesh Pro only; per-player canvases
- Data: ScriptableObjects in `Assets/Resources/`; JSON via `QuestJsonLoader`, `ShopTradeJsonLoader`
- Input: `InputSystem_Actions.inputactions` (no hardcoded keycodes)

# MCP (Unity / ai-game-developer)
- When MCP tools are available (e.g. ai-game-developer server connected to Unity), **use them** for Unity-related tasks: inspecting scenes, GameObjects (e.g. CENTER, Model_Bakunawa), components, hierarchy, and running Unity commands. Prefer MCP tools over guessing scene or inspector state.
- If the user asks to check or fix something in a Unity scene, try MCP tools first when the server is enabled.

# Unity workflow
- Do **not** create Unity Editor tools (menu items, editor windows, custom inspectors) unless the user explicitly asks for them. If they need something set up in Unity, they will say so; prefer adding setup steps to existing docs (e.g. BAKUNAWA_SETUP.md) instead.
- Do **not** create new `.md` (or other documentation) files unless the user explicitly asks for one.

# Output
- Minimal edits; preserve formatting. No reformat or rename unless asked.
- Avoid new packages or `.meta` changes unless requested.

# Validation Checklist
For gameplay/transition changes, verify:
- no compile errors
- host/client both complete transition
- local player spawns once and lands on correct spawn marker
- loading screen lifecycle is correct
- input and camera control return correctly after cutscene/transition
- inventory events fire correctly (no double subscription, UI updates on add/remove/equip)
- quest progress applies for all players individually (Collect/TalkTo)
